title: Independent Candidate Liaqat Ali wins PB-43 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Liaqat Ali has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-43, Quetta-VI by securing 7,277 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Sardar Douda Khan who bagged 5,190 votes.
Overall voters turnout remained 30.42 percent.
